Name: ICU
URL: https://github.com/unicode-org/icu
Revision: 7708a760c001c5e0d546430ad18007620aea04e7
Security Critical: yes

License: MIT
License File: ../../../../../third_party/icu/default/LICENSE

Description:
  This file has the relevant components from ICU copied to handle basic
  UTF8/16/32 conversions. http://site.icu-project.org/

  Revision was estimated via looking at the nearest commit prior to the date of:
  https://source.corp.google.com/h/fuchsia/fuchsia/+/30d4108d4e9dc0056db9580bd4f517691a83b5fd

Local Modifications:
  Components are copied from utf.h utf8.h utf16.h and
  utf_impl.c The same module appears in third_party/icu, so we don't repeat the license
  file here.The main change is that U_/U8_/U16_ prefixes have been replaced with
  FXL_U_/FXL_U8_/FXL_U16_ to avoid confusion with the "real" ICU macros should ICU
  be in use on the system. For the same reason, the functions and types have been
  put in the "fxl_icu" namespace.

  This library has been exempted from third party freshness requirements, and is
  now being treated as first-party library. See https://fxbug.dev/526720299
